
To execute Cochise you will need root privileges.
1. go into the bin directory
2. execute export JAVA_OPTS="-DcochisePass=YourPassword"
   (replace YourPassword with a password of your choice, you will be asked for it later)
2. execute "startup.sh"
3. now You can reach Cochise via http://IP_Of_Your_Server:12080/WebGUI-0.1.0-RC1/ with your web-browser
4. if you are done execute "shutdown.sh"

WARNING:
1. Cochise may be accessible from the outside!
2. For now only plain HTTP is configured, that means the access to Cochise is not secure!
